DOC.brief_summary: This clinical study is a prospective, post-market-clinical-follow-up study to investigate the long-term (3 months) safety of femtosecond laser assisted cataract surgery as a study follow-up extension to the Study #1304 titled as "A Multi-centre, Multi-surgeon, Randomized, Controlled, Prospective, Post-Market-Clinical-Follow-Up Study to Investigate the Impact of Cataract Grade on the Efficacy and Safety of Femtosecond-laser Assisted Lens Fragmentation Procedure".
DOC.brief_title: Long-term (3 Months) Safety of Femtosecond-laser Assisted Cataract Surgery
DOC.criteria: Only the patients who were successfully enrolled in Study #1304 are eligible for this followup extension study.
